        <desc>Shabara is a dark world south of the Burnished Plains where the sun loses its power. Giant Floating Plates made of the same material as the Emperor's Palace hang high in the sky, shrouding the land in gloom as they slowly shift and turn. The plates are broken and fragmented, and areas between these shapes where light filters through are somehow brighter and hotter than the rest of the World and burn those who cross. Citizens of the Land of Broken Sky do not recognize the ruling cities and pay no tribute, and incursions into the Land of Broken Sky have proved devastatingly unsuccessful. Nevertheless, its citizens are content to trade and socialize with members of the tributaries.</desc>
